<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
WORKERS APPREHEND 2 BURGLARY SUSPECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two construction workers in Thousand Oaks captured two teen-agers Wednesday 
allegedly in the act of burglarizing a single-family home and trapped them in a 
bathroom. 
</P>
<P>
Derian Drickerson, 23, and Rafael Ariztia, 25, came to the rescue of Carolina 
Kosashi after she ran from her house on the 600 block of Triunfo Canyon Road at 
11:30 a.m. screaming about burglars, said Lt. Kelli McIlvain of the Ventura 
County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Kosashi had arrived home and heard voices in the house, McIlvain said. 
</P>
<P>
Drickerson and Ariztia, both of the Newbury Park area of Thousand Oaks, entered 
Kosashi's house and caught two of three suspects upstairs, McIlvain said. A 
third suspect fled the house, which had been ransacked, he said. Possessions 
had been stacked, McIlvain said. 
</P>
<P>
Drickerson and Ariztia held the two suspects -- a male and a female, both of 
Northridge -- in the bathroom until officers arrived and arrested them, 
McIlvain said. 
</P>
<P>
Drickerson and Ariztia also were able to describe the car of the third suspect. 
Police arrested Friedrick Widjajawiguna, 18, of Northridge on suspicion of 
burglary moments later. He was carrying a few possessions believed to be from 
the Kosashi house, McIlvain said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
