<P>
BIDS ON DRAINAGE PROJECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County officials will open bids May 8 on the first of two drainage 
projects planned in Pacific Palisades, a spokesman for Supervisor Deane Dana 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The project calls for the placement of 2,500 feet of reinforced concrete pipe 
between Capri Drive and the Santa Monica Canyon channel near Sunset Boulevard, 
spokesman Dennis Morefield said. Work is expected to begin in July and be 
completed by December, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Plans call for a second, 3,900-foot segment in the area north of Capri Drive to 
be installed later, he said. 
