<DOCNO> LA041990-0144 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 206581 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 19, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Part A; Page 7; Column 3; Foreign Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
22 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPACE FLIGHT FOR A GERMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West Germany and the Soviet Union signed an agreement Wednesday to send a 
German astronaut to the Mir space station in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
SPACE PROGRAMS -- WEST GERMANY; USSR -- FOREIGN RELATIONS -- WEST GERMANY; 
JOINT VENTURES; ASTRONAUTS; MIR (SPACE STATION) 
</P>
