<TEXT>
<P>
The Chicago Bears said published reports had exaggerated the amount of taxes in 
dispute between the Internal Revenue Service and the team's owners. 
</P>
<P>
The National reported that the IRS was seeking about $43.5 million in gift and 
inheritance taxes stemming from a 1981 reorganization of the team. The 
newspaper said interest and penalties could drive the assessment to more than 
$50 million. 
</P>
