<HEADLINE>
<P>
TONIGHT'S MEDFLY SPRAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State helicopters are scheduled tonight to resume spraying malathion over a 
36-square-mile section that includes all of Garden Grove, and parts of 
Huntington Beach, Los Alamitos, Cypress, Stanton, Anaheim, Orange and Santa 
Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Frank Parsons, Orange County agricultural deputy commissioner, said the 
spraying is subject to change, depending on weather conditions. Spraying is set 
to begin about 9 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Malathion spraying in an eight-square-mile section of Brea was canceled Monday 
night because of rain. Spraying of that area has been rescheduled for Saturday 
night. Tonight's aerial spraying will be the fourth time that the controversial 
pesticide has been used in the Garden Grove area, where two Mediterranean fruit 
flies were found late last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
