<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LA QUINTA WINS VOLLEYBALL MATCH, REMAINS ON TOP IN GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rancho Alamitos High School boys' volleyball team had a chance to gain a 
tie for first place in the Garden Grove League, but La Quinta defeated the 
Vaqueros in four games to retain sole possession. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Douherty had 17 kills to lead La Quinta to a 15-5, 15-13, 9-15, 15-8 
victory. La Quinta is 10-1 overall, 9-0 in league. Rancho Alamitos is 7-2 in 
league. 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League matches: 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 3, Los Amigos 0 -- Joe Squyres had 10 kills and Alex Ripley had 10 
blocks as host Garden Grove (8-7, 5-4) won, 15-3, 15-8, 15-10. 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 3, Santiago 1 -- Tony Kennedy had 11 kills to lead Pacifica to a 15-3, 
10-15, 15-10, 15-13 victory. 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Foothill 3, Cypress 0 -- John Newcomb had seven kills and Scott McKittrick had 
six to lead Foothill (10-1, 5-0) to a 15-1, 15-5, 15-9 victory at Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 3, Santa Ana 1 -- Mike Bradach had 17 kills and 10 stuff blocks and 
El Dorado (5-4, 3-2) won, 8-15, 16-14, 15-2, 15-6, at Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 3, Fountain Valley 1 -- Scott Jahr had six kills and Ted Barsh 
had four kills to lead host Huntington Beach (8-2, 4-1) to a 15-0, 15-5, 11-15, 
16-14 victory. 
</P>
