In Sea View League boys' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 126, Saddleback 24 -- Dietrich Jewell won the 500 free in 
4:55.23, the 200 free in 1:54.4 and helped Newport Harbor's 400 free relay win 
in 3:22.20. Newport Harbor is 5-2, 4-0. 
</P>
<P>
In Sea View League girls' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 102, Saddleback 32 -- Jennifer Bloomfield, Jenny Pence, Allison 
Jones and Maureen McLaren helped Newport Harbor qualify for the Southern 
Section preliminaries in the 400 freestyle relay (3:57.36). 
</P>
<P>
In Empire League girls' swimming: 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos 116, El Dorado 38 -- Los Alamitos (7-1, 4-0) won every event at El 
Dorado. Nicole Williamson won the 100 butterfly (1:01.82) and the 100 
breaststroke (1:09.3). 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague golf: 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 400, Sunny Hills 409 (18 holes) -- Andy Rothman shot three-over-par 75 
to lead Estancia (10-1) at Los Coyotes. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 409, Foothill 437 (18 holes) -- Kengo Takahashi shot four-over 76 for 
Valencia (13-0) at Santa Ana County Club. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange League boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Western 18, Anaheim 0 -- The team of Anand Jethva and Tom Tran won its doubles 
sets, 6-0, 6-0, 6-0, for Western (12-2, 7-2) at Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 17, Magnolia 1 -- The team of Jason Bae and Chris Seki , won its sets, 
6-4, 6-1, 6-0, for host Valencia (13-1, 10-0). 
</P>
<P>
In Sea View League boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
University 15, Estancia 3 -- No. 2 singles player John Bowerbank (7-6, 6-0, 
6-0) swept for host University (10-3, 6-1). 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 16, Saddleback 2 -- Grant Michaelson swept, 6-2, 6-0, 6-1, to 
lead visiting Corona del Mar (13-2, 8-0). 
</P>
<P>
In Empire League boys' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 11, Katella 7 -- The No. 1 doubles team of Dan Harris and Jim Stewart 
swept, 6-2, 6-0, 6-0, for visiting Esperanza (12-3, 6-0). 
