<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LA QUINTA WINS NO. 300 FOR DEMAREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coach Dave Demarest gained the 300th victory of his career when La Quinta High 
School defeated Garden Grove, 6-1, in a Garden Grove League game Wednesday at 
La Quinta. 
</P>
<P>
Demarest has coached 17 years at La Quinta and has a record of 300-120. This 
season, La Quinta is 14-6 and 6-1 in league. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Logan had two hits, including a bases-empty home run in the fourth inning, 
scored twice and had two RBIs to lead La Quinta. 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League games: 
</P>
<P>
Los Amigos 4, Santiago 2 -- John Morgan (5-5) pitched a three-hitter and 
doubled in Los Amigos' third run in the seventh inning. Los Amigos (7-12, 5-2) 
scored four in the inning and had seven doubles in the game. Marco Perez hit a 
two-run home run in the fifth for Santiago (5-2 in league). 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 3, Bolsa Grande 2 -- Romeo Ponteres and Servin Nosek combined 
for a one-hitter for host Rancho Alamitos (4-12, 2-5). Ponteres (1-3) pitched 5 
2/3 innings and Nosek finished with hitless relief for the save. Jim Gamez 
scored the winning run in the third inning on Chris Osterade's single. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 5, Pacifica 3 -- Visiting Pacifica led, 3-0, before Kennedy's four-run 
rally in the fourth, capped by Craig Roah's two-run double. Kennedy is 9-11, 
4-3. 
</P>
<P>
In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 2, Cypress 1 (9 innings) -- Jon Pitts scored from second on a 
throwing error during a double-play attempt in the bottom of the ninth for 
Esperanza (14-4, 8-0). Cypress scored a run in the seventh inning to tie the 
score. 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 8, Loara 3 -- Matt Svoboda (1-1) pitched a one-hitter, striking out 
10 and walking eight, to lead El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
Katella 5, Los Alamitos 2 -- John Allen pitched a six-hitter to lead visiting 
Katella (14-4, 5-3). Mike Farley hit a bases-empty home run for Katella. 
</P>
<P>
In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 6, Fullerton 3 -- Rick Orr (5-2) pitched a seven-hitter and struck 
out six to lead host Sunny Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Troy 7, Buena Park 3 -- Brent Coon had two hits, two stolen bases and three 
RBIs; Matt Carter had two hits and scored three runs and Guy Pinelli (3-2) 
pitched a complete game and had eight strikeouts to lead visiting Troy (7-8, 
4-3). 
</P>
<P>
La Habra 5, Sonora 3 (9 innings) -- Mike Martin and Jason Johnson singled in 
the ninth inning and both scored on a throwing error following a sacrifice bunt 
for visiting La Habra. Mark Moreno hit a bases-empty home run in the sixth and 
pitched nine innings, allowing four hits and striking out 12 for La Habra 
(4-11, 3-5). Scott Oxarart struck out eight for Sonora. 
</P>
<P>
In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 6, San Clemente 4 -- Mark Huffman had two hits and a stolen base and 
Scott Brendino had two RBIs for host Irvine (10-9, 5-3). 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 4, Mission Viejo 0 -- Travis Burgus (5-2) pitched a 
two-hitter, walking eight and striking out 13, and Danny Zamora had two hits, 
two RBIs and two stolen bases for visiting Capistrano Valley (10-7-1, 3-4-1). 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 5, Dana Hills 4 -- Reggie Watkins had two hits and scored a run, and 
Darren Sharp had a two-run double to drive in two of El Toro's three runs in 
the third. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 7, Saddleback 3 -- Rees Thorkelson hit a three-run double in the 
first, went two for four with four RBIs and pitched a complete game for 
visiting Corona del Mar (7-11, 2-6). 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 15, University 6 -- Ruben Mora went four for four and Paul McDaniels 
was two for three with four RBIs, including a three-run home run in the seventh 
inning. 
</P>
