<HEADLINE>
<P>
MULTIFAMILY HOME FUTURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Elena Brunet / Los Angeles Times; Graphics by Doris 
Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Permits for the construction of multiple-family housing units (duplexes, 
apartments, condominiums) opened stronger this year than 1988 or 1989. 
January's total of 600 such permits put 1990's first month 67% ahead of last 
year and 57% more than 1988. None of the last three years, however, have come 
close to the totals issued in January, 1986, and January, 1987. A major 
increase in permits for Irvine lead the increased activity. 
</P>
