<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNCIL DELAYS DECISION ON SUING BROOKINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Delaying a decision on whether to sue Bishop H.H. Brookins, the Los Angeles 
City Council on Wednesday directed the city attorney's office to negotiate with 
Brookins in a dispute over $48,000 he may owe the city. 
</P>
<P>
The council gave the order during a closed session and continued the matter 
until May 11, Councilman Robert Farrell said. 
</P>
<P>
At issue is $48,000 in Community Development Department funds paid to a 
Brookins organization to rent a building that Brookins owned. 
</P>
<P>
The CDD has concluded that the money is owed to the city because Brookins had a 
conflict of interest in his dual role as a landlord who collected city rent for 
his property while serving as the head of a poverty program located in the 
building. 
</P>
</TEXT>
