<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNTY CLERK ZOLIN TO LEAVE POST NEXT MARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Frank S. Zolin, who runs the largest original jurisdiction court system in the 
English-speaking world, announced Wednesday that he is leaving his job as Los 
Angeles County clerk and Superior Court executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
Zolin, 57, said in a resignation letter to county supervisors and Superior 
Court Presiding Judge Richard P. Byrne, that after 32 years of government 
service he wishes to pursue new professional opportunities. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm 57 years old, and I think I've got eight or 10 very productive years 
before I want to play golf all the time," Zolin said. 
</P>
<P>
He added that he may pursue consulting opportunities or another management 
position in the public or private sector. Zolin said he plans to leave in 
March, 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
