FINGER LAKE TRACK PACT OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CANANDAIGUA, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Management and horsemen at Finger Lakes race track have agreed to a two-year 
contract extension, clearing the way for this weekend's opening of the 1990 
season, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Under terms of the contract extension agreed on Wednesday, members of the 
Horsemen's Benevolent Protective Assn. will receive the same compensation they 
received under an agreement that expired Dec. 31, 1989. However, the extension 
will be subject to review after the 1990 season if average daily handle falls 
below last season's handle. 
</P>
<P>
The season, which opens Saturday with post time at 1:15 p.m., was delayed eight 
racing days because of construction at the track and contract negotiations. 
</P>
